                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>Each time a swallowed creature begins their turn, they are affected by this horrific curse. If a creature escapes being swallowed whole before reaching stage 5, it recovers fully from this curse at the start of its next turn.</p>\n<p><strong>Saving Throw</strong> @Check[will|dc:25]</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 1</strong> @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Stupefied]{Stupefied 1} (1 round)</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 2</strong> @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Stupefied]{Stupefied 2} and @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Slowed]{Slowed 1} (1 round)</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 3</strong> @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Stupefied]{Stupefied 3} and slowed 1 (1 round)</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 4</strong> stupefied 3 and @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Slowed]{Slowed 2} (1 round)</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 5</strong> the target's intellect is permanently reduced below that of an animal, and it treats its Charisma, Intelligence, and Wisdom modifiers as –5; it loses all abilities that require mental faculties, including spellcasting (unlimited duration).</p>"
                },
